{"lemma": "اِسْتٌ", "slug": "اِسْتٌ", "root": "س.ت.ه", "root_slug": "س-ت-ه", "root_link": "/words/roots/س-ت-ه", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n724", "n18852", "n18887"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A7%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "rump", "fa": "دُم", "ur": "گودا", "tr": "kuyruk", "id": "pantat", "bn": "পিঠ", "es": "nalgas", "fr": "fesses", "de": "Gesäß", "ru": "ягодицы", "zh": "臀部"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "rump; buttocks"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "rump; buttocks; anus"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "first, beginning, foundation", "examples": [{"text": "اِسْتُ الدَّهْرِ", "english": "the beginning of time"}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Unclear.\nConceivably from Proto-Semitic *ʔišd- (“backside, lower leg, base, foundation”), and related to Classical Syriac ܐܫܬܐ (eštā, “base, bottom, buttocks”), Ugaritic 𐎌𐎚 (št), Hebrew שֵׁת (šēṯ), and Akkadian 𒁼 (išdum, “base, foundation, root”), then related to Arabic أُسّ (ʔuss) and أَسَاس (ʔasās), both meaning base or foundation."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n724", "headword_ar": "اِسْتٌ", "root": "Ast", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", signifying The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "podex,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "anus,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,) or signifying the former, and sometimes used as meaning the latter, (S in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sth", "text_ar": "سته"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) is with a conjunctive hemzeh, [written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@sotN", "text_ar": "ا@سْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", when not immediately preceded by a quiescence,] and its final radical letter is clided; for the original form is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "satahN", "text_ar": "سَتَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb;) and it is mentioned in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sth", "text_ar": "سته"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) [It is of the fem. gender.] It is said in a prov., applied to him who fails of attaining the object that he seeks,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^axoTaA^ati A@sotuhu AlHuforapa", "text_ar": "اَخْطَاَتِ ا@سْتُهُ الحُفْرَةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His anus missed the hole in the ground"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Meyd.) — [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aisotu Ald~ahori", "text_ar": "اِسْتُ الدَّهْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The first,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "beginning, of time;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "old,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ancient, time."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IB, A, * K. *) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA zaAla EalaY A@soti Ald~ahori majonuwnFA", "text_ar": "مَا زَالَ عَلَى ا@سْتِ الدَّهْرِ مَجْنُونًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He ceased not,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has not ceased, from the beginning of time,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from old time, to be insane,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mad;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he always was,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "always has been, known as being insane,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mad:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "like as one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A_is~i", "text_ar": "عَلَى اـِسِّ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~ahori", "text_ar": "الدَّهْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (AZ, S.) And Aboo-Nukheyleh says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "maA zaAla mu*o kaAna EalaY A@ soti Ald~ahori\n                      \n                     \n                        *aA HumuqK yanomiY waEaqolK yaHor$Y"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He ceased not,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has not ceased, to be, since he was in the beginning of time,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in old time,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the first of his existence, a person of increasing foolishness, and of decreasing intellect"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (AZ, S.) IB says, J has erred in mentioning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this section [of the S]; its proper place being in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sth", "text_ar": "سته"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", where he has also mentioned it; for its hemzeh is conjunctive, by common consent; and if conjunctive, it is augmentative: also, his saying that they have changed the [final]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_is~N", "text_ar": "اـِسٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "t", "text_ar": "ت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as they have changed the [final]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tas~N", "text_ar": "طَسٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "t", "text_ar": "ت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", making this word"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TasotN", "text_ar": "طَسْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", is a mistake; for, were it so, the hemzeh of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "would be disjunctive [in every case; whereas it is always conjunctive except after a pause, when it is pronounced with kesr]: moreover, he has attributed this assertion to AZ, who never made it, but only mentioned"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast Aldhr", "text_ar": "است الدهر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "As~ Aldhr", "text_ar": "اسّ الدهر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because of their agreement in meaning. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence also,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aisotu Alkalobapi", "text_ar": "اِسْتُ الكَلْبَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Calamity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "misfortune:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "adversity; difficulty; distress; affliction:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what is hated, disliked, disapproved, foul, abominable,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "evil."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aisotu Almatoni", "text_ar": "اِسْتُ المَتْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The desert:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the wide desert."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-  See also art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sth", "text_ar": "سته"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["K", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n18852", "headword_ar": "اِسْتٌ", "root": "st", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see arts."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sth", "text_ar": "سته"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": it is properly mentioned in the latter art., being originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "satahN", "text_ar": "سَتَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, TA.)"}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n18887", "headword_ar": "اِسْتٌ", "root": "sth", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh, K, written with the conjunctive hemzeh, Msb in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "satahN", "text_ar": "سَتَهٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S Mgh, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "satohN", "text_ar": "سَتْهٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sitohN", "text_ar": "سِتْهٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(CK [but not in my MS. copy of the K nor in the TA, and of doubtful authority, as will be seen from what follows,]) signify the same, (S, * Mgh, * K,) i. e. The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "podex, buttock"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "buttocks, posteriors, rump,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "croup;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and sometimes the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "anus;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S;) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "satahN", "text_ar": "سَتَهٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being the original form, as is shown by the pl., (S, Mgh,) which is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asotaAhN", "text_ar": "اَسْتَاهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Mgh, K;) like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jamalN", "text_ar": "جَمَلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ajomaAlN", "text_ar": "اَجْمَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": it may not be [↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sitohN", "text_ar": "سِتْهٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sutohN", "text_ar": "سُتْهٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ji*oEN", "text_ar": "جِذْعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qufolN", "text_ar": "قُفْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", of which the pls. are also of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afoEaAlN", "text_ar": "اَفْعَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", because, when you restore the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "which is the final radical, and reject the medial radical [which is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "t", "text_ar": "ت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sahN", "text_ar": "سَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with fet-h, (S, Mgh, *) which has both of the meanings expl. above, as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suhN", "text_ar": "سُهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) but [SM says,] this last, mentioned by the author of the K, is strange, and I have not seen it on the authority of any one [else]: (TA:) and some say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "satN", "text_ar": "سَتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (IKh, S, Mgh, TA,) suppressing the final radical [of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "satahN", "text_ar": "سَتَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (S,) i. e., without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h", "text_ar": "ه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "at the end and without hemzeh [or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A", "text_ar": "ا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] at the beginning. (TA.) [All are of the fem. gender.] It is said in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEayonu wikaA='u Als~ahi", "text_ar": "العَيْنُ وِكَا=ءُ السَّهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or, as some relate it,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~ati", "text_ar": "السَّتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Mgh, TA,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The eye is the tie of the anus,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] meaning that when one [closes the eye and] sleeps, the tie of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sah", "text_ar": "سَه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "becomes loosed, and the excrement and wind issue. (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abuw", "text_ar": "اَبُو"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^asotaAhi", "text_ar": "الاَسْتَاهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He who has large posteriors."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Az, TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biA@soti fulaAnK", "text_ar": "بِا@سْتِ فُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a phrase of the Arabs significant of reviling; (S;) said when holding one in contempt; meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laSiqa AlEaAru biA@soti fulaAnK", "text_ar": "لَصِقَ العَارُ بِا@سْتِ فُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May disgrace cleave to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of such a one"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mgh.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA A@bona A@sotihaA", "text_ar": "يَا ا@بْنَ ا@سْتِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O son of her"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (K, TA,) a prov. of the Arabs, (TA,) is an allusion to one's father's"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHomaAD", "text_ar": "اـِحْمَاض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[see 2 in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HmD", "text_ar": "حمض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] of the former's mother; (Z, TA;) and is said to mean"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^an~ahu wulida mini A@sotihaA", "text_ar": "اَنَّهُ وُلِدَ مِنِ ا@سْتِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) and the Arabs called the sons of the female slave"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banuw A@sotihaA", "text_ar": "بَنُو ا@سْتِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Sh, TA.) And one says to a man who is deemed abject and weak,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aisotu A^um~ika A^aDoyaqu", "text_ar": "اِسْتُ اُمِّكَ اَضْيَقُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thy mother's"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is too contracted"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aisotuka A^aDoyaqu mino A^ano tafoEala ka*aA", "text_ar": "اِسْتُكَ اَضْيَقُ مِنْ اَنْ تَفْعَلَ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wa ka*aA", "text_ar": "وَ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thine"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is too contracted,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thine ability is too small, for thy doing such and such things"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (TA: [see also Freytag's Arab. Prov., i. 607:]) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anotumo A^aDoyaqu A^asotaAhFA mino A^ano tafoEaluwhu", "text_ar": "اَنْتُمْ اَضْيَقُ اَسْتَاهًا مِنْ اَنْ تَفْعَلُوهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in like manner] is an allusion to inability [meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Ye are unable to do it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (K.) The saying of a poet,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "wa A^anota makaAnuka mino waAy^ilK\n                      \n                     \n                        makaAnu AlquraAdi mini A@soti Aljamalo"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And thou, thy place in the tribe"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Wáïl is"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "like"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the place of the tick in the rump of the camel,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is tropical; for they do not [properly] say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aisotu Aljamali", "text_ar": "اِسْتُ الجَمَلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eajuzu Aljamali", "text_ar": "عَجُزُ الجَمَلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) One says also to a man who is deemed low, or base,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anota AlAisotu Als~ufolaY", "text_ar": "اَنْتَ الاِسْتُ السُّفْلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ant Alsb~ahu Als~ufolaY", "text_ar": "انت السبَّهُ السُّفْلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thou art"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "among others"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the condition of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of mankind: (S, TA:) and of low, or base, men, one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`w^ulaA='i AlA^asotaAhu", "text_ar": "هٰوُلَا=ءِ الاَسْتَاهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and of such as are excellent,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`w^ulaA='i AlA^aEoyaAnu", "text_ar": "هٰوُلَا=ءِ الاَعْيَانُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alwujuwhu", "text_ar": "الوُجُوهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) And one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqiytu minohu A@sota Alkalobapi", "text_ar": "لَقِيتُ مِنْهُ ا@سْتَ الكَلْبَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A, K,) a prov., (TA,) meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I experienced from him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, what I disliked,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hated."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, K, TA. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov., ii. 445.]) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aisotu AlbaAy^ini A^aEorafu", "text_ar": "اِسْتُ البَايِنِ اَعْرَفُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEolamu", "text_ar": "اَعْلَمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "byn", "text_ar": "بين"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA laka A@sotN maEi A@sotika", "text_ar": "مَا لَكَ ا@سْتٌ مَعِ ا@سْتِكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thou hast no one"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with thee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to assist thee:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, K, TA:) another prov., related on the authority of AZ as said to one who has no large amount of property, nor number of men. (Sgh, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tarakotuhu biA@soti", "text_ar": "تَرَكْتُهُ بِا@سْتِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aroDi", "text_ar": "الاَرْضِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", another prov., (TA,) meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I left him destitute, poor,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "possessing nothing:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tarakotuhu biA@soti Almatoni", "text_ar": "تَرَكْتُهُ بِا@سْتِ المَتْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I left him on the hard ground, alone."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Meyd.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA laka fiY h`*aA", "text_ar": "مَا لَكَ فِى هٰذَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^amori A@sotN wa laA famN", "text_ar": "الاَمْرِ ا@سْتٌ وَ لَا فَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thou hast not in this thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "affair, root nor branch:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "Jereer says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "famaA lakumu A@sotN fiY AlEalaA='i wa laA= famu"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1306}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And ye have not any root in eminence, nor branch"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAna *`lika EalaY A@soti Ald~ahori", "text_ar": "كَانَ ذٰلِكَ عَلَى ا@سْتِ الدَّهْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That was in the beginning of time:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, K, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the olden time;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AO, S, TA;) as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A_is~i Ald~ahori", "text_ar": "عَلَى اـِسِّ الدَّهْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (AO, TA.) See also art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ast", "text_ar": "است"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". [And see other exs. in Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 355 and 378 (a variation of a prov. mentioned in the preceding page) and 607 and 622 and 729-730.]"}], "source_refs": ["K", "S", "Mgh", "TA", "IKh", "A"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}